Privacy Policy
Introduction
By accessing or using AirByte's iOS, Mac, and other client applications (“Apps”), websites, services, and other content provided by AirByte Tech. ("we", "us", or "our"), you agree to the collection and use of your information as detailed in this Privacy Policy.
Consent and Data Collection
We prioritize your privacy and do not gather personally identifiable information (such as your name, email, phone number, or address) without your explicit consent for the normal operation of our Apps. If you choose to provide us with personal information (e.g., by contacting us via email), you consent to our collection and use of that information for the functionality of our Apps and Services.
We may require your personal data to address support requests. Additionally, we may inform you about our services, including new features, special offers, and updates. Users have the option to opt out of such communications.
Third-Party Analytics
We utilize third-party analytics providers such as Apple, Google, and Yahoo to gather statistics on how our applications are used. This includes usage data, frequency of use, and crash reports in the event of errors. This information helps us understand user behavior, resolve technical issues, and improve our products.
Third-party providers collect, use, and disclose your information only to the extent necessary to perform their services for us.
Data Sharing and Disclosure
We do not sell, trade, or transfer your personally identifiable information to outside parties without providing advance notice, except for trusted partners who assist in operating our website and apps, conducting our business, or serving our users. We may also release your information when necessary to comply with the law, enforce site policies, or protect our rights, property, or safety.
Non-personally identifiable visitor information and statistics may be shared with other parties for marketing, advertising, or other purposes.
External Links
Our Apps or websites may contain links to external sites. We are not responsible for the privacy practices of other sites and encourage you to read their privacy policies.
Cookies and Tracking Technologies
When you visit our websites, we collect usage information sent by your device that indicates how you are using the sites ("usage information"). We employ various tracking technologies to gather this data. Cookies and similar technologies help with system administration, fraud prevention, security improvements, and enabling shopping cart functionality. We do not require your consent for cookies that are strictly necessary.
We use cookies and tracking technologies to assess our site's effectiveness and enhance your experience. Google Analytics session cookies help us generate meaningful reports about site visitors in aggregate.
Updates to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. Changes will take effect immediately upon being posted on our website. While we may attempt to notify you of major changes, we recommend reviewing the Privacy Policy regularly. Your continued use of our Apps and Services after any changes indicates your acceptance of the updated policy.
Contact Information
For any questions regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact us through our website.
Effective Date
This Privacy Policy was last updated on April 25, 2024.